===Etymology===
{{unc|zh}}.
* {{zh-ref|Bodde (1975)}} cites {{w|Zheng Xuan}}'s comment on the relation between {{och-l|臘|year-end sacrifice}} and {{och-l|獵|hunt}};
* {{zh-ref|Boltz (1979)}} instead relates it to a much later word written with the same phonetic & meaning "to cut off, to terminate" (of a year);
* {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007)}} proposes an alternative {{der|zh|sit}} etymology: just as the {{och-l|葉}} word-family encompasses the meanings "leaf > foliage, year, generation"; so the root *''râp'' "new year, change of year" is apparently a parallel etymon, which also is cognate with {{cog|bo|རབས།||generation}} ({{zh-ref|Bodman, 1980}}).

